  "texts": [
    "Extreme gradient boosting (XGB), random forest (RF), and extra tree classifier (ETC) are the foundations of the proposed ensemble model, and a voting mechanism is used to determine the final prediction.",
    "• The KNN (K closest neighbour) imputer is used in studies to produce missing values to address the issue of missing values.",
    "• The Principal Component Analysis (PCA) is utilized to impute missing values on considering feature importance.",
    "• Different machine learning models, including RF, LR (logistic regression), GBM (gradient boosting machine), GNB (Gaussian Naive Bayes), ETC, SVC (support vector classifier), DT (decision tree), and SGD (stochastic gradient descent), are used to compare their performances.",
    "The performance of the suggested model is compared against cutting-edge methods in terms of accuracy, precision, recall, and F1 score to assess its efficacy."
  ],
